Profile of Bay bottom along adopted line is indicated by heavy black, hatched line. Elevations of bottom were
obtained by numercus soundings along adopted line

Borings AD,C,D & E were made n proper positions along adopted line to clearly define the top elevations of the
characteristic sand stratum thot forms the geological foundation of the Bay. Borings A & B were located near the
main piers of the channel span, and define the top of sand stratum under these structures Profile of top of sand
etratum olong adopted line 15 indicated by heavy, dashed line

Borings | to 18, incl. were made along an allernate line about one mile north of the adepted line. Study of geoleg-
ical stratification of Doy bottom indicotes regulority, which is supported by Borings A to E incl. For that reason Bor-
ngsdl to 18,inclu. have been projected to the adopted line and are shown in detail as closely representative of exact
